CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 21, 1947, pg. 17, reads: "Now in East - Billy Eckstine, the bronze balladeer, who recently completed a stand as a single at Billy Berg's in Hollywood, drove cross-country to New York, where he will remain for several days prior to opening an engagement at the Bengasi in Washington as well as lining up other dates in East. Billy paused at his home in Pittsburgh en route to New York. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Bandleader and musician Billy Eckstine posing with Cadillac convertible car, on street in residential neighborhood
